I am trying to understand an example from my textbook. Let's say $Z = X + Y$ , where $X$ and $Y$ are independent uniform random variables with range $[0,1]$ . Then the PDF
is $$f(z) = \begin{cases}
z & \text{for $0 < z < 1$} \\
2-z & \text{for $1 \le z < 2$} \\
0 & \text{otherwise.}
\end{cases}$$ How was this PDF obtained? Thanks

